\begin{equation}\label{eq:tcl}
    \mathrm{TCL}_H(\tau|\boldsymbol{Z}, G_H) 
        = \prod_{b=1}^B \prod_{\mathbf{z}_{[H]}\in G_H} f(\mathbf{z}_{[H]}^{(b)};\tau),
\end{equation}
and can be regarded as an exponentially weighted composite likelihood in which weights are binary. The performance of the truncated likelihood estimation can be improved when $G_H$ consists of correlated components. Algorithm \ref{algo:graph} is a pseudo-algorithm for generating $G_H$ for given $\delta$ and $q_G$.

